JSP standard tag library

	bundle of tags that accomplish core func of a web app
	comes in a jar, has to be added to <u>build path</u>

has modules:
	core module:
		iteration, conditional statement, display data
	formatting module
		format values (date, weight...), localization (logging in one place ...), internationalization (make app location everywhere)
	xml module:
		manipulating xml
	sql module
		querrying db with sql

	core module: <c:name of tag/>
	xml module: <x:name of tag/>
	sql module: <sql: name of tag/>
	fmt module: <fmt: name of tag/>
Note: to use the modules, you need to include them independently.
	JSTL is aligned to EL so you can use EL in them

syntax for including JSTL:
<%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core" prefix="c"%>
<%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/fmt" prefix="fmt"%>
<%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/sql" prefix="sql"%>
<%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/xml" prefix="x"%>